---
import DocsLayout from "../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro";
import CodeBlock from "../../components/CodeBlock.astro";
import Callout from "../../components/Callout.astro";

const mainEntry = `import { WompiClient } from "@pulgueta/wompi";`;

const serverEntry = `import { getSignatureKey, type GetSignatureKeyOptions } from "@pulgueta/wompi/server";`;

const schemasEntry = `import {
  // Zod schemas — validate request bodies before they hit the SDK.
  CreateTransactionInputSchema,
  TokenizeCardInputSchema,
  CreatePaymentLinkInputSchema,
  // Inferred types — every z.output<…> shape, zero runtime cost.
  type Transaction,
  type TransactionStatus,
  type CreatePaymentLinkInput,
  type Result,
  // Error classes — for instanceof checks.
  WompiError,
  WompiNotFoundError,
  WompiValidationError,
  WompiRequestError,
} from "@pulgueta/wompi/schemas";

// Validate an incoming form body before passing it to the SDK.
const parsed = CreateTransactionInputSchema.safeParse(req.body);
if (!parsed.success) return res.status(400).json(parsed.error.flatten());`;
---

<DocsLayout
  section="Reference"
  title="Package exports"
  description="Every entry point @pulgueta/wompi ships and what's behind it."
>
  <p>
    The package is published as ESM and CJS with separate type declarations for each subpath. Pull
    in only the entry you need — the others stay out of your bundle.
  </p>

  <h2 id="main">
    <code>@pulgueta/wompi</code>
  </h2>
  <p>
    The default entry. Exports the client and nothing else — instantiate it once and reach every
    resource through it.
  </p>
  <CodeBlock code={mainEntry} lang="ts" />
  <ul>
    <li>
      <code>WompiClient</code> — the high-level client constructed in every other doc page. It runs
      on the platform <code>fetch</code>, so it works in Node and edge runtimes alike.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="server">
    <code>@pulgueta/wompi/server</code>
  </h2>
  <p>
    The server-only helpers. Houses <code>getSignatureKey</code>, the integrity signature builder,
    plus its options type. Kept in its own entry so a browser bundle never pulls in the signing
    logic.
  </p>
  <CodeBlock code={serverEntry} lang="ts" />
  <ul>
    <li>
      <code>getSignatureKey</code> — computes the SHA-256 integrity signature
      <code>createTransaction</code> requires. See <a href="/docs/integrity-signature">Integrity
        signature</a>.
    </li>
    <li><code>GetSignatureKeyOptions</code> — the argument type for the helper above.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="schemas">
    <code>@pulgueta/wompi/schemas</code>
  </h2>
  <p>
    Everything type-related lives here: the raw Zod schemas, the inferred TypeScript types they
    produce, the error classes and the <code>Result</code> tuple. Pull schemas in to validate a
    request body in your own routing layer, types in to annotate your code, or error classes in for
    <code>instanceof</code> branching.
  </p>
  <CodeBlock code={schemasEntry} lang="ts" />

  <Callout type="tip" title="Typed enums">
    <code>TransactionStatus</code>, <code>PaymentMethodType</code> and <code>LegalIdType</code>
    are string literal unions — perfect for narrowing in <code>switch</code> statements. Import the
    type and skip the schema entirely.
  </Callout>

  <p>
    See <a href="/docs/error-handling">Error handling</a> for the two ways to branch on the error
    classes exported here.
  </p>

  <h2 id="summary">Subpath summary</h2>
  <table>
    <thead><tr><th>Subpath</th><th>Exports</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><code>.</code></td><td><code>WompiClient</code></td><td>The default entry — the client and nothing else.</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>./server</code></td><td><code>getSignatureKey</code>, <code>GetSignatureKeyOptions</code></td><td>Web Crypto, server-only.</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>./schemas</code></td><td>Zod schemas, inferred types, error classes, <code>Result</code></td><td>For validation layers, type annotations and <code>instanceof</code> checks.</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
</DocsLayout>
